did this on regular basis, and if so maybe you can give some tips. I tried this for first time yesterday (never been on the islands yet &amp; I'm 54, hehe).<br>
I quad kite wyverns all the time in CS so not new to the game, so thought I would give these fellers a try. Wow, takes some patience to do these. Nice XP but took me like 5 mins juts to get all rounded up and finally all snared. Then the problem was, unlike wyverns when they are almost dead, the seafuries scatter apart, forcing me to finish them singly, draining mana, having to root park 1-2 remainders. I believe the XP may be better than wyverns, but I could quad 2x fast in CS though. I found SOW is almost a must with these guys ( I have jboots, took forever to get distance built up). Are these guys just that much harder or am I missing a needed strategy here, just curious. Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzedrick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zedrick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/27/01 8:47:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding sea furies in OOT</span><hr size=1> If you are feeling brave, you can use an Al'Kabor spell in this situation.  It really is a trade off with the mana/damage ratio, but sometimes it's cheaper to blow you're last bub of mana on an Al'Kabor spell than to finish them off as singles.  I've used this tactic quading Rhino's in Eastern Wastes, and it works sometimes, sometimes it doesn't.<br>
<br>
-Zedrick <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubranamanstarbinder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branaman Starbinder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/27/01 9:36:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding sea furies in OOT</span><hr size=1> I tried it at 54 with 209 INT and 315 in mana items and had to med to finish them. <br>
<br>
Seafuries are not very social and one partial means the rest wanders off while one is still after you. <br>
<br>
Pulling and rounding them up is not that hard, just lev above the water to round them up, run back to the shore and snare them there. <br>
<br>
If I am correct then 5 Pillars of lighting should do the trick. Stay on shore all the time, sometimes a bump in the shoreline will let you miss a target so watch out for that.<br>
<br>
I stick to 2 or sometimes 3 of them. 4 seafuries give too much trouble to be worth the effort. <p><center>There used to be a signature here, but the site hosting it, my provider, decided to delete all personal homepage directories.<br><table><tr>
